text: In the song “Enchanted” by Taylor Swift, the narrator has encountered someone who they feel a strong connection to. They describe the feeling of being in the same room as this person, a “tired, lonely place” that has become filled with emotion and warmth when they meet. The narrator talks about feeling wonderstruck and enchanted to meet this person, wishing that this is the start of a love story rather than its concluding chapter. They pray to not have anyone else fill their heart and plead for the chance to be together. Taylor Swift’s song encourages the listener to take a chance and take joy in the delightful moments found in life.

text: It was a dream of mine which had brought me back to the point where I was hopeless. She stood out there in my neighbour so beautiful and as calm as ever walking past me with her eyes down as always. Tho she was never my neighbor I never felt anything was off as it was a dream. As she walk past me the ME in my dream was also a part of me and subsequently had a feeling of awkwardness and a strong feeling of devotion with a little bit of sadness.Then after that I'm pretty sure she walk past me one more time and this time she looked at me but only with her head down. How beautiful her eyes we're. Long lashes with her big eyes only partly visible due her facing down and looking a bit up to glare at me with only with embarrassment.Then there as we somehow happened to meet outside after few mins saw her little sister maybe of around 12 driving a car. It was weird but a dream. She drove pretty well for a 12 yr old kid. Then she told me "only I can sit while my sister is driving ", I was pretty amazed her sister could drive a car and that word added more amazement in my head.She was but a kid, she started to lose balance and I had to handle it. It was not hardwork i jz had to hit the brakes as it was moving ahead on its own. This scene was maybe my desire to impress her. But i never heard anything from her there.Maybe an indication that she talked less. Then there I saw this little embarrassment in her eyes and throwing a letter at me told " This is my reply ".Here it connects my dream to the reality where I had given her a letter in school and she never sent a reply back. I already had an idea what her reply would be (obviously a turndown) was but excited. Then I had put it in my pocket and had decided to read when i was free. Going down stairs I met my mom she had seen through me and asked hows it going between us only for me to reply that I didn't know. I can still imagine how beautiful she looked in my mind while I was answering my mom. And then i never opened the letter in my dream. Maybe another indication that I never got a reply from her.
